PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F355A1776881466
OL,3,CKirkstone Pass landslide repairs start
OL,5,FCouncillor Peter Thornton, Westmorland
OL,6,Fand Furness Council's Cabinet member
OL,7,Ffor Highways, said: "The landslip has
OL,8,Foccurred in a very challenging and
OL,9,Frestricted location, with steep
OL,10,Fbanking above and below, and it's not
OL,11,Fthe easiest place to access,
OL,12,Fespecially during the winter months."
OL,14,FMeasures were taken to stabilise the
OL,15,Fground and divert water away from the
OL,16,Farea to prevent further collapse, but
OL,17,FWestmorland and Furness Council said
OL,18,Fat the time it needed to find a
OL,19,Fcomplex engineering fix to make the
OL,20,Froad safe again. Diversion routes and
OL,21,Fsignage have been in place ever since.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G2/6
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
